# reserved / empty for now.
# A script would be justified only by a mechanical image-markup check: a raw `<img ` used for
# content, a `next/image` with neither `width`/`height` nor `fill`, or more than one `priority`
# per route. The blocker is false positives — the check must tell a content image from a
# decorative/icon one, and the "always-sized" rule is perf-adjacent rather than one of the nine.
# Add one here only once that content/decorative distinction is reliable and no sibling
# (rule-audit Rule 3/4) already owns it. This skill is image-pipeline judgment, not a lint.
